Matthew Wyldbore (c.1716- 15 March 1781) was a British politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1768 to 1780
He was baptised on 15 April 1716 at St John the Baptist Church, Peterborough.
He was educated at Newcome's School in Hackney and entered Trinity College, Cambridge on 26 June 1733, aged 17.
He was also admitted at Inner Temple on 27 March 1735.
Wyldbore served as Whig Member of Parliament for Peterborough, 1768–1780.
For many years, he was a member of the Bedford Level Corporation.
He left a bequest for a peal of bells on the anniversary of his death, a tradition which continues each 15 March.
